node.text:
Fire those LEG & BUTT🔥 - this one is a MUST try if you still at home or no access to weights room. SAVE & TAG your bff 👯‍♀️ - don't be selfish LMAO 😏
.
OKAY, now who else is READY to kick some a** and start the week strong?! 🙋🏻‍♀️ If you are interested in workouts that are EFFECTIVE (no cookie butter plan or magic tricks 🙄 like we can see on the internet) Email me or click link in bio. I only work with the serious ones!
.
Grab your bands and 2 gallon of water, if you have that perfect, if you don't grab something heavy from around!
.
Workout instructions:
.
No rest between exercises
60 sec rest after each rounds
There are 4 total. 
GW = Gallon water E/S= each side
.
1️⃣ GW BANDED PULSES SQUAT WALK - 10 steps total (get 2 low pulses at low squat)
2️⃣ RESISTED BAND 3/4 SUMO SQUATS - 10 total + 10 BANDED JUMPS
push backwards against the bands as you come up - squeeze you butt and abs - you will feel it a LOT
3️⃣ SINGLE LEG HAMMIE LYING CURL - 10 E/S do these slow & controlled, the hamstring and glutei should be fired up 
4️⃣ GW BANDED B-STANCE SQUAT SIDE LEG LIFT - 10 E/S (use a light to medium band - I did use the strongest and then It was too hard LOL.  its about form not else…)
Your bodyweight is on the fix leg, squat down, lift your leg up + squeeze your glutes as you come high. You can tap down the floor to help with balance.
5️⃣ SQUAT BAND SIDE TOE TAPS - 5 reps E/S
(3 taps = 1 rep, so repeat 5x and then move onto the other leg.
6️⃣ LYING SINGLE LEG HAMMIE CURL - 10E/L (husband didn’t do a very good job filming this sorry lol) - do these slow controlled, make sure to feel it in your hamstring!
7️⃣ LYING CURL - 10 leg together - Control those and squeeze at the top🔥
.

.

node.text:
Do 3 sets of 15 reps 30 sec rest

Workout description 
1. Start with the abs are they are the foundation of your body, on an decline bench, if you don’t have a ViRP, dumbbell or a bar will do the work too .
.
2. Follow by L-seat ring legs should be 😆 90° or above from the floor. Always keep control of your body. The challenge here is to move and maintain stability: HI SHOULDER MUSCLES! .
.
3. Reverse grip face pull: you fire up not only your back but your core and your Lower body by the isometric contraction...! Super efficient to get your back strong, defined and powerful shoulders!
.
4. Pyramidal deadlift, consists of increasing the weights as set go! Keep your core tight, back remains straight, eyes look in the same direction as your body move up and down (does it make sense? 😅) .
.
5. T bar squat, I do a sumo version  because I felt more comfortable that way. Find the best stance for yourself. Increase weight as well until the last 2-3 reps are difficult.... .
.

node.text:
In France 🇫🇷 & happy to be here eating croissants 🥐& tasty food…. 🥰

Being in shape doesn’t always mean that you need to stay in the shape you’re in, but accepting and loving each part of the journey whatever your goal might be.

This is not your “Instagram perfect” body, not the typical “bounce back” post we often see from other people out of the industry I belong to. 

Some times we fall out of shape, and then we go back to it. Matter of fact, it’s not a “bounce back” post at all.

Every step of my & your journey is unique and a new beginning with a NEW TRANSFORMATION
And I am transforming FORWARD; not back.

Stronger, better and wiser.
Evolving and growing to became a better version of myself through committed HARD WORK, old and new knowledge and with a unbreakable confidence in both my work ethic and overall capability and understanding of the parts when I’ve got my post surgeries transformations, or time when I couldn’t be there mentally. 

Six pack isn’t something I’m looking for like my life was depending on it - like it was before. Who feel guilty of that? Today it’s about feeling good inside and out. Being in harmony with my lifestyle and my mental health. If your mind is happy and drive is strong you’ll be in shape by results. 

The important thing is to find the beauty in each stage, and to confidently accept and love yourself throughout the whole journey.

Can you guess my weight today?

node.text:
I got asked what your tattoo represents. Here my explanation: The sun reflects off the dark cloud. To those who can see the top or back of the cloud, the reflection is so bright that the cloud appears to be lined with silver. The sun is always shining. It shines in the day. It shines in the night. It shines when the day is clear. It shines when the clouds are dark. We can’t see the sun at night because it’s on the other side of the earth, but it is still shining. We can’t see the sun when the dark clouds hang low, but the sun is still shining behind the dark clouds, creating a silver lining. In every dark cloud there is a silver lining…. ☀️ 
Plus it brings warmth, fire 🔥 (the one inside of me fighting passionately for something, or burning what’s toxic to me) and with a bit of spirituality it brings me to love ❤️…. 

Do you have tattoos? What do they represent? 

To end on a fun note: 🤪 If you don’t have - tag someone you know with hair (can be a pet - mustache accepted), 4 limbs, who can walk or run, make noise with their mouth, affectionate, who eat a lot or not, who nap but work also… I need to see where all those tags will bring me : SURPRISE 😂 

Happy Wednesday 😙😘

You can lift every weight in the gym, but if you can't move your body, what's the point? 

If you’re agreed type 💯 
Tag / share with a friend 🙏

Being able to flex your mobility is an important part of a healthy lifestyle—even if mastering the movements used to hone your abilities isn't always easy.

The challenge that comes with pushing your body to move in new, different ways.. This is a double whammy because it's great warmup exercise and a great bodyweight exercise in general. 

Admittedly, when first doing those crab variations it's a little uncomfortable 😬. We rarely open up our bodies in this position (arms extended back, opening up the chest and hip extension)—which is why it's so deliciously good.

The crab reach can help out anyone with tight hip flexors, particularly those of us who sit all day in an office or don’t stretch enough 😆 since it's a chest and shoulder opener 💯

To perform the move, you just need some space on the floor to spread out. Start out with the crab lift and upgrade to the crab reach 👍 3 sets of 10 reps (gradually you’ll change as you’ll get stronger!

I’ve spent half of my life not allowing myself to be happy unless and until… But the unless and until never came perfect each time.  So I was waiting. Eventually I realized that you will never be happy until you have the ability to be happy with what you have. Right now. In the moment.

Striving for more in a thing but waiting for the perfect moment - that will never come its another. As you build a better life, this ability is a practice. A daily one. Because we all snap back to tying our happy to things we dont have and event that havent happened. 

Accept your story. Where you are at in life and everything that lead you to here. Nothing is permanent. Appreciate and give yourself credit on how far you have come. Anything is possible even if it hasn’t happen yet. Trust your process and do the best you can. It always workout if it means to be right? 

If you relate double tap and comment Y-E-S letter by letter without being interrupted or tag a friend (still to work on maintaining this high algorithm of mine) 😜
